cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.CR

The paper deals with analyzing human trails on the Web, which involves understanding user behavior and predicting user clicks. This falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Cybersecurity (cs.CY), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). However, since the paper focuses on modeling and comparing hypotheses about human trails using Bayesian inference, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI, followed by cs.IR and cs.CL. The other two sub-categories are less likely but still relevant due to the potential security implications of analyzing user behavior on the Web.
